<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab turvaettev&otilde;tete ning asutuste, ettev&otilde;tete ja organisatsioonide (edaspidi organisatsioon) sisevalveteenistuste, samuti &uuml;ksikisikute tegevuse tingimused ja korra j&auml;rgmiste alaliste v&otilde;i ajutiste turvateenuste osutamisel v&otilde;i turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the procedure and conditions for the activities of security undertakings, and internal guarding services of agencies, enterprises and organisations (hereinafter organisations), and of individuals in the provision of the following permanent or temporary security services and in the performance of the following security tasks: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vallas- ja kinnisvara valve ja kaitse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) guarding and protection of movable and real property; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikukaitse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) personal protection; </inglise>
<eesti>3) veoste valve ja kaitse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) guarding and protection of cargo; </inglise>
<eesti>4) korra kindlustamine tellija v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;ritustel ja objektidel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) ensurance of order at events organised by and objects belonging to customers and employers; </inglise>
<eesti>5) turvakonsultatsioon ja -uuringud objekti puutumatuse ja ohutuse tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) consultation and research in the field of security to ensure the inviolability and safety of objects. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvaettev&otilde;tetele ning turvateenuseid osutavatele &uuml;ksikisikutele laienevad k&otilde;ik ettev&otilde;tlust reglementeerivad seadused koos k&auml;esolevast seadusest tulenevate erisustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) All Acts which regulate enterprise apply to security undertakings and individuals providing security services with the specifications resulting from this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolev seadus ei k&auml;sitle kaitsej&otilde;udude ja politsei tegevust objektide valve ja kaitse tagamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This Act does not regulate the activities of the Defence Forces and the police in ensuring the guarding and protection of objects. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses kasutatakse m&otilde;isteid allj&auml;rgnevas t&auml;henduses: </eesti>
<inglise>In this Act, the following definitions are used: </inglise>
<eesti>1) turvateenistuse subjekt - turvaettev&otilde;te, sisevalveteenistus ja turvateenuste osutamisega tegelev &uuml;ksikisik; </eesti>
<inglise>1) "subject of security service" means a security undertaking, internal guarding service or individual engaged in the provision of security services; </inglise>
<eesti>2) turvaettev&otilde;tlus - ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i &uuml;ksikisiku tegevus turvateenuste osutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) "security enterprise" means the activities of undertakings and individuals in the provision of security services; </inglise>
<eesti>3) turvateenus - k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 1 1.l&otilde;ike punktides 1-5 nimetatud teenus, mida osutab turvaettev&otilde;tlusega tegelev isik; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "security service" means a service specified in clauses 1 (1) 1) -5) of this Act provided by a person engaged in security enterprise; </inglise>
<eesti>4) turva&uuml;lesanne - k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 1 1.l&otilde;ike punktides 1-5 nimetatud &uuml;lesanne, mida t&auml;idab sisevalveteenistus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) "security task" means a task specified in clauses 1 (1) 1) -5) of this Act performed by an internal guarding service; </inglise>
<eesti>5) turvateenistus - turvateenistuse subjektide tegevus turvateenuste osutamisel v&otilde;i turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>5) "security service" means the activities of a subject of security service in the provision of security services or performance of security tasks; </inglise>
<eesti>6) turvalitsents - riiklik tegevuslitsents, mis annab turvateenuste osutamise v&otilde;i turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise &otilde;iguse; </eesti>
<inglise>6) "security licence" means a state activity licence which grants the right to provide security services or perform security tasks; </inglise>
<eesti>7) valveobjekt - inimene, vara, veos, ruum, ehitis, rajatis, territoorium v&otilde;i muu asi, kelle v&otilde;i mille valveks ja kaitseks on turvateenistus suunatud, samuti valveobjektil v&otilde;i seal l&auml;biviidaval &uuml;ritusel viibimise v&otilde;i k&auml;itumise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>7) "guarded object" means a person, property, cargo, premises, a structure, a construction, a territory or another thing for the guarding or protection of which security services are directed, and the procedure for being present at and for conduct at a guarded object or an event carried out at a guarded object; </inglise>
<eesti>8) isikukaitse - t&auml;iskasvanud isiku soovil tema v&otilde;i ta alaealise lapse ohutuse tagamiseks rakendatud meetmete kogum; </eesti>
<inglise>8) "personal protection" means a set of measures applied at the request of an adult person in order to ensure the safety of the person or his or her child who is a minor; </inglise>
<eesti>9) valve - tegevus valveobjekti ja selle &uuml;mbruse j&auml;lgimisel, ohu v&otilde;i kallaletungi avastamiseks objektile v&otilde;i objekti puutumatuse tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>9) "guarding" means activities in monitoring a guarded object and its surroundings in order to detect any threat to or attack against the object or to ensure the inviolability of the object; </inglise>
<eesti>10) kaitse - meetmete rakendamine valveobjekti &auml;hvardava ohu v&otilde;i r&uuml;nde t&otilde;kestamiseks ning puutumatuse tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>10) "protection" means the application of measures to combat imminent threat to or attack against a guarded object and to ensure the inviolability of the object; </inglise>
<eesti>11) tehniline valve - valveseadmete ja h&auml;ires&uuml;steemide kogum valveobjekti puutumatuse j&auml;lgimiseks ja r&uuml;nnete avastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>11) "electronic security equipment" means a set of security equipment and alarm systems used for surveillance of a guarded object and for detection of security violations; </inglise>
<eesti>12) h&auml;ires&uuml;steem - signalisatsiooniseadmete ja -ahelate kogum h&auml;iresignaali edastamiseks valveobjektilt; </eesti>
<inglise>12) "alarm system" means a set of signal devices and chains to forward alarm signals from a guarded object; </inglise>
<eesti>13) tsentraliseeritud h&auml;ires&uuml;steem - signalisatsiooniseadmete ja -ahelate kogum h&auml;iresignaali edastamiseks ja registreerimiseks mitmelt valveobjektilt. </eesti>
<inglise>13) "centralised alarm system" means a set of signal devices and chains to forward alarm signals from several guarded objects. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Objekti turvalisuse tagamise korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of ensurance of security of objects </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Organisatsioonid korraldavad vahetult neile kuuluva v&otilde;i nende valduses oleva vara, territooriumi ja muu objekti turvalisuse (valve ja kaitse) tagamist k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Organisations shall organise ensurance of the security (guarding and protection) of property, territories and other objects directly in their ownership or possession pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mainitud eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;ib organisatsioon moodustada oma koosseisus spetsiaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse - sisevalveteenistuse - v&otilde;i kasutada lepingu alusel turvaettev&otilde;tlusega tegeleva isiku teenuseid, samuti kasutada tehnilist valvet ja teenistuskoeri. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to achieve the aforementioned objective, an organisation may form a special structural unit (internal guarding service) within its composition or, on the basis of a contract, use the services of a person engaging in security enterprise, or use electronic security equipment or service dogs. </inglise>
<eesti>(28.06.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 62, 1056) </eesti>
<inglise>(28.06.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 62, 1056) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;ib kehtestada m&otilde;nda liiki objekti tehnilise kindlustatuse ning turvalisuse tagamise erin&otilde;uded: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Government of the Republic may establish special requirements for the use of electronic security equipment and ensurance of the security of some classes of objects, as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valitsusasutustele ja riigiettev&otilde;tetele, samuti muudele organisatsioonidele, mille tegevus on seotud k&otilde;rgendatud ohuga inimestele v&otilde;i keskkonnale; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on government agencies and state enterprises, and on other organisations the activities of which involve increased danger to human health or the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&otilde;rgendatud ohustatusega objekti vastu suunatud kuritegeliku r&uuml;nde t&otilde;kestamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) in order to combat criminal attacks against objects subject to increased danger. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Valveobjekti turvalisuse tagamise viisid </eesti>
<inglise>Manners of ensuring security of guarded objects </inglise>
<eesti>Valveobjekti turvalisust tagatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>The security of guarded objects shall be ensured: </inglise>
<eesti>1) turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajate poolt vahetult; </eesti>
<inglise>1) directly by the security staff; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tehnilise valve abil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) by means of electronic security equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teenistusloomade abil. </eesti>
<inglise>3) with the aid of service animals. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenistuse subjekti p&otilde;hi&uuml;lesanded ja tegevuspiirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Principal functions and restrictions on activity of subject of security service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvateenistuse subjekti &uuml;lesandeks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The function of a subject of security service is to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valveobjekti ohutuse ja puutumatuse tagamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) ensure the safety and inviolability of a guarded object; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valveobjekti vastu suunatud v&otilde;i seda ohustava &otilde;iguserikkumise ennetamine, t&otilde;kestamine ja t&otilde;rjumine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) forestall, prevent and combat offences directed against or endangering a guarded object; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valveobjekti vastu suunatud &otilde;iguserikkumise s&uuml;ndmuskoha puutumatuse tagamine. </eesti>
<inglise>3) ensure the inviolability of the scene of an offence directed against a guarded object. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvateenistuse subjektil ei ole &otilde;igust t&auml;ita riigikaitse v&otilde;i politsei v&otilde;imkonda kuuluvaid funktsioone. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subjects of security service do not have the right to perform functions which belong within the powers of national defence or the police. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvaettev&otilde;te </eesti>
<inglise>Security undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvaettev&otilde;tteks k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on ettev&otilde;te, millel on litsents turvateenuste osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a security undertaking is an undertaking which holds a licence to provide security services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvaettev&otilde;te ei tohi tegelda relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona tootmise, hulgi- v&otilde;i jaem&uuml;&uuml;giga ning eradetektiivteenuste osutamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Security undertakings shall not engage in the production, wholesale trade or retail sale of weapons or ammunition or in the provision of private detective services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turvaettev&otilde;te peab olema registreeritud ettev&otilde;ttena Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A security undertaking shall be registered in Estonia as an enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;ib kehtestada piiranguid v&auml;liskapitali osaluse kohta turvaettev&otilde;tte vara koosseisus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Government of the Republic may establish restrictions on foreign capital in the composition of the assets of security undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turvalitsents annab turvaettev&otilde;ttele &uuml;htlasi &otilde;iguse sisevalveteenistuse korraldamiseks ettev&otilde;ttes endas. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A security licence also grants a security undertaking the right to organise an internal guarding service within the undertaking itself. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisevalveteenistus </eesti>
<inglise>Internal guarding service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sisevalveteenistus valvab ja kaitseb objekte, mida organisatsiooni juht (juhtorgan) on valveobjektiks m&auml;&auml;ranud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An internal guarding service guards and protects objects which the head (management body) of the organisation has designated as guarded objects. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sisevalveteenistus v&otilde;ib valvata ja kaitsta ainult oma organisatsiooni objekte, sealhulgas kaitsta organisatsiooni t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An internal guarding service shall guard and protect only the objects of the corresponding organisation and protect the employees of the organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;ib ta ilma viimase loata kaitsta juhul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus on isikukaitse tagamine ette n&auml;htud. </eesti>
<inglise>An employee may be protected without his or her permission if personal protection is prescribed in the contract of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sisevalveteenistus peab turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks omama turvalitsentsi vaid Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An internal guarding service is required to hold a security licence to perform its duties only in the cases prescribed by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja </eesti>
<inglise>Security guard </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on turvaettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i sisevalveteenistuse juht, turvaala juhtivt&ouml;&ouml;taja ning t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes vahetult valvab ja kaitseb valveobjekte, samuti &uuml;ksikisik, kellel on &otilde;igus turvateenuste osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a security guard is a head or senior security official of a security undertaking or internal guarding service, an employee of a security undertaking or internal guarding service who directly guards and protects guarded objects, or an individual who has the right to provide security services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valvur on turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes ei oma &otilde;igust teostada isikukaitset ning valvata ja kaitsta neid valveobjekte, mille loetelu kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A guard is a security guard who does not have the right to provide personal protection or to guard and protect objects specified in the list established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>Valvurina v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada 18-65-aastane Eesti alaline elanik. </eesti>
<inglise>Any permanent resident of Estonia between 18 and 65 five years of age may work as a guard. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajana v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada 20-65-aastane isik, kes on Eesti kodanik, omab vastavat kvalifikatsioonitunnistust ja turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaarti ning on aus ja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rne. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Any person between 20 and 65 years of age who is an Estonian citizen, who holds an appropriate qualification certificate and a security guard identification card and who is honest and trustworthy may work as a security guard. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;ksikisik, kes soovib osutada turvateenuseid, peab vastama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. v&otilde;i 3.l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An individual who wishes to provide security services shall comply with the requirements prescribed in subsections (2) or (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajana ei ole &otilde;igust t&ouml;&ouml;tada isikul: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The following do not have the right to work as security guards: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kes kannab karistust v&otilde;i omab karistatust tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person who is serving a sentence or has a criminal record for an intentionally committed criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kes tegeleb relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona tootmise, hulgi- v&otilde;i jaem&uuml;&uuml;giga v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tab eradetektiivina; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who is engaged in the production, wholesale trade or retail sale of weapons or ammunition or who works as a private detective; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kes on politseiametnik v&otilde;i t&auml;itevametnik; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person who is a police officer or custodial official; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kes on kaitsev&auml;e teenistuses; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person who serves in the Defence Forces; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kelle vabastamisest politsei teenistusest mittevastavuse t&otilde;ttu oma ametikohale v&otilde;i distsipliinirikkumise eest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hem kui viis aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a person who has been released from police service due to his or her unsuitability for his or her position or for a violation of discipline if less than five years have passed since his or her release; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kes on vabastatud teenistusest lojaalsusvande rikkumise t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a person who has been released from service for violation of the loyalty oath; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kes on vabastatud politseist, turvaettev&otilde;ttest v&otilde;i sisevalveteenistusest usalduse kaotuse t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>7) a person who has been released from the police, a security undertaking or an internal guarding service due to loss of confidence. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3.l&otilde;ike n&otilde;uded kvalifikatsioonitunnistusele ja turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaardile ei laiene sisevalveteenistuse turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes ei ole kohustatud turvalitsentsi omama. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The requirements of subsection (3) of this section concerning the qualification certificate and security guard identification card do not apply to a security guard of an internal guarding service who is not required to hold a security licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uded turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajatele ning vastava kvalifikatsioonitunnistuse v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i tema poolt volitatud ametkond. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Qualification requirements for security staff and the procedure for the issue of corresponding qualification certificates shall be established by the Government of the Republic or an agency authorised thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaart </eesti>
<inglise>Security guard identification card </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajale (v&auml;lja arvatud valvur), kes vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 8 m&auml;rgitud n&otilde;uetele, v&auml;ljastatakse turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaart elukohaj&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuri poolt turvaettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i sisevalveteenistust omava organisatsiooni juhi (juhtorgani) taotlusel, samuti &uuml;ksikisiku avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A security guard (except a guard) who meets the requirements specified in &sect; 8 of this Act shall be issued a security guard identification card by the police prefecture of his or her residence on the basis of an application submitted by the head (management body) of a security undertaking or an organisation which has an internal guarding service or on the basis of an application made by an individual. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajate kaartide v&auml;ljaandmise, kehtivuse peatamise ja t&uuml;histamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i tema poolt volitatud ametkond. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for the issue, suspension and revocation of security guard identification cards shall be established by the Government of the Republic or an agency authorised thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvalitsents. </eesti>
<inglise>Security licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenuste osutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of security services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvaettev&otilde;te v&otilde;ib turvateenuseid osutada turvalitsentsi omamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A security undertaking may provide security services if it holds a security licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvaettev&otilde;ttele ja sisevalveteenistusele antakse turvalitsents, kui on tuvastatud, et taotlejal on seaduslikuks ja n&otilde;uetekohaseks turvateenuste osutamiseks v&otilde;i turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks piisavalt vahendeid, teadmisi, oskusi, kogemusi ja personali. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A security undertaking or an internal guarding service shall be issued a security licence if it is ascertained that the applicant has necessary means, expertise, skills, experience and personnel to provide security services or perform security tasks in a lawful manner and pursuant to requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;ksikisik v&otilde;ib turvateenuseid osutada turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaardi omamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An individual may provide security services if he or she holds a security guard identification card. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turvateenistuse subjekt v&otilde;ib osutada neid turvateenuseid v&otilde;i t&auml;ita neid turva&uuml;lesandeid, mis on lubatud turvalitsentsi v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaardiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A subject of security service may provide the security services or perform the security tasks permitted by the security licence or security guard identification card. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turvalitsentse annab v&auml;lja politseiprefekt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Security licences shall be issued by police prefects. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Juhul kui turvateenistus, v&auml;lja arvatud veoste valve ja kaitse, h&otilde;lmab mitme politseiprefektuuri teenistuspiirkonda, antakse turvalitsents politsei peadirektori poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a security service, except the guarding and protection of cargo, covers the service areas of several police prefectures, the security licence shall be issued by the national police commissioner. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Turvalitsentside v&auml;ljaandmise kehtivuse peatamise ja t&uuml;histamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The procedure for the issue, suspension and revocation of security licences shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Turvateenuseid osutatakse ainult kirjaliku lepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Security services shall be provided only on the basis of written contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Turvateenuste osutamise v&otilde;i turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega seotud dokumentatsiooni koostamise ja hoidmise korra ja t&auml;htajad kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The procedure and terms for the preparation and storage of documentation related to the provision of security services and the performance of security tasks shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Turvalitsentsi ei v&auml;ljastata ettev&otilde;ttele, mille omaniku v&otilde;i omanike m&otilde;ne teise turvaettev&otilde;tte turvalitsents on t&uuml;histatud seaduserikkumise v&otilde;i usalduse kaotuse t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) A security licence shall not be issued to an undertaking if the owner or owners of the undertaking own another security undertaking, the security licence of which has been revoked due to an offence or lack of trust. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirangud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions upon performance of duties </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenistuse subjektil: </eesti>
<inglise>A subject of security service does not have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei ole &otilde;igust t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel heli-, foto-, kino-, video-, side-, valve- ja muud tehnikat kasutades rikkuda kellegi p&otilde;hiseaduslikke &otilde;igusi ja vabadusi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) violate any person's constitutional rights or freedoms by using audio, photographic, cinematographic, video, communications, security or any other type of technology in the performance of its duties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei ole &otilde;igust teostada operatiivj&auml;lituslikke toiminguid. </eesti>
<inglise>2) take operative surveillance measures. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenistuse subjekti ja turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of subject of security service and of security staff </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenistuse subjekt v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja: </eesti>
<inglise>Subjects of security service and security staff: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on kohustatud hoidma saladuses temale seoses turvateenuste osutamise v&otilde;i turva&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega teatavaks saanud &auml;ri- v&otilde;i muud informatsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) are required to maintain the confidentiality of business secrets and other information of which they become aware in the provision of security services or performance of security tasks; </inglise>
<eesti>2) peab informeerima koheselt politseid k&otilde;igist valveobjekti vastu toimepandud, toimepandavatest v&otilde;i kavandatavatest kuritegudest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) shall immediately inform the police of any criminal offence which has been committed, is being committed or is planned against a guarded object; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei tohi oma tegevusega takistada riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsuse organite ja asutuste, riikliku kontrolli- ja j&auml;relevalveorganite, kohtueelse uurimise organite, kohtute ning ametiisikute tegevust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) shall not, with their activities, hinder the activities of state and local government bodies and agencies, state control and supervisory bodies, pre-trial investigation authorities, courts and officials; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ei tohi tegutseda poliitilistel eesm&auml;rkidel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) shall not act for political purposes; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ei tohi oma tegevuse k&auml;igus lubada endale teiste isikute au ja v&auml;&auml;rikust alandavat kohtlemist, rikkuda eluruumi puutumatust, kirjavahetuse-, riigi- v&otilde;i &auml;risaladust ning muid p&otilde;hiseadusega kaitstud &otilde;igusi ja vabadusi. </eesti>
<inglise>5) shall not, in the course of their activities, degrade the honour or dignity of other persons, breach the inviolability of a dwelling, violate the duty to maintain the confidentiality of correspondence and state or business secrets, or violate any other rights or freedoms protected by the constitution. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of security staff </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Security staff have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&otilde;kestada p&auml;&auml;s valvatavale objektile isikutel, kes p&uuml;&uuml;avad sinna siseneda vastava loata v&otilde;i seadusliku aluseta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) prevent access to a guarded object by any person who attempts to enter the object without an appropriate permit or legal grounds; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kinni pidada isikuid, kes ebaseaduslikult tungivad v&otilde;i on tunginud valvatavale objektile v&otilde;i viibivad seal vastava loata v&otilde;i seadusliku aluseta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) apprehend any person who unlawfully enters or has entered a guarded object or stays there without an appropriate permit or legal grounds; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kinni pidada isikuid, kes oma k&auml;itumisega ohustavad valveobjekti turvalisust v&otilde;i segavad turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajat tema &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) apprehend any person who endangers the security of a guarded object or hinders performance of the duties of security staff by his or her behaviour. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;ltuvalt kinnipeetava poolt toimepandud teo iseloomust on turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Depending on the nature of the act committed by an apprehended person, security staff have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kinnipeetav objektilt &auml;ra saata; </eesti>
<inglise>1) escort the apprehended person from the object; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tuvastada kinnipeetava isik kohapeal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) identify the apprehended person on site; </inglise>
<eesti>3) anda kinnipeetav viivitamatult &uuml;le politseile isiku tuvastamiseks ning vajalike meetmete v&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) hand the apprehended person promptly over to the police for identification and for necessary measures to be taken. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Tehniline valve </eesti>
<inglise>Use of electronic security equipment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vabariigi Valitsusel on &otilde;igus kehtestada tehnilise valve seadmete ja h&auml;ires&uuml;steemide projekteerimise, paigaldamise ja hooldamise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Government of the Republic has the right to establish the procedure for the design, installation and maintenance of electronic security equipment and alarm systems. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tsentraliseeritud h&auml;ires&uuml;steemide ehitamise ja kasutamise korra, kui selle s&uuml;steemi toimimine on seotud &uuml;ldkasutatava traatside, samuti raadiosidega, kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for the construction and use of centralised alarm systems, provided that the functioning of such systems is connected to public telecommunications or radio communication, shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvad ja erivahendid </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons and special equipment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvateenistuse subjekt v&otilde;ib relvaseadusega etten&auml;htud alustel ja korras soetada ja hoida relvi ja laskemoona ning neid v&auml;lja anda kandmiseks oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A subject of security service may acquire and store weapons and ammunition and issue weapons and ammunition to be carried by its employees on the bases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by the Weapons Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvateenistuse subjekt v&otilde;ib objekti valveks ja kaitseks kasutada j&auml;rgmisi erivahendeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A subject of security service may use the following special equipment to guard and protect objects: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kaitsekiivreid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) protective helmets; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kuulikindlaid veste; </eesti>
<inglise>2) body armour; </inglise>
<eesti>3) eriotstarbelisi m&auml;rgistus- ja v&auml;rvimisseadmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) special purpose marking and colouring equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&auml;eraudu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) handcuffs; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teenistuskoeri. </eesti>
<inglise>5) service dogs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turvateenistuse subjektile lubatud erivahendite liigid (k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ige) ja arv, nende soetamise, hoidmise, kandmise ja kasutamise tingimused ja kord ning n&otilde;uded erivahenditele kehtestatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse v&otilde;i tema volitusel siseministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The classes of special equipment permitted to a subject of security service (subsection (2) of this section), the amount of such equipment, the conditions and procedure for the acquiring, storage, carrying, wearing and use of such equipment, and the requirements for the special equipment shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic or, on the authorisation thereof, by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Erivahendi kasutamise juhtude registreerimise ja politseile teatamise kord kehtestatakse siseministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The procedure for registration of cases where special equipment is used and the procedure for informing the police thereof shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turvalitsentsi t&uuml;histamisel, turvaettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamisel ning sisevalveteenistuse likvideerimisel kuuluvad turvaettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i sisevalveteenistuse omandis olevad erivahendid realiseerimisele kolme kuu jooksul, arvates litsentsi t&uuml;histamisest, turvaettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;ppemisest v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamisest ning sisevalveteenistuse likvideerimisest korras, mille kehtestab siseminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon revocation of a security licence, dissolution or termination of a security undertaking or liquidation of an internal guarding service, the special equipment in the ownership of the security undertaking or internal guarding service shall be sold, pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Internal Affairs, within three months as of the revocation of the licence, the dissolution or termination of the security undertaking or the liquidation of the internal guarding service. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhul kui erivahendid realiseerib politseiasutus, h&uuml;vitab realiseerimise kulud turvateenistuse subjekt. </eesti>
<inglise>If the special equipment is sold by a police authority, the subject of security service shall compensate the cost of the sale. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui erivahendeid ei &otilde;nnestu realiseerida nimetatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, kuuluvad need h&auml;vitamisele korras, mille kehtestab siseminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If special equipment cannot be sold within the specified term, it shall be destroyed pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(28.06.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 62, 1056) </eesti>
<inglise>(28.06.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 62, 1056) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja vormiriietus ning dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Uniform and documents of security staff </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja vormiriietuse kirjeldus ja kandmise kord kinnitatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A description of and the procedure for wearing the uniforms of security staff shall be approved pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajal peab t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel kaasas olema turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaart, turvaettev&otilde;tte ja sisevalveteenistuse turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajal aga ka t&ouml;&ouml;t&otilde;end. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the performance of their duties, security staff shall carry a security guard identification card and security guards employed by security undertakings and internal guarding services shall also carry a certificate of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti peab tal kaasas olema n&otilde;utav luba kaasasoleva relva v&otilde;i erivahendi kandmiseks v&otilde;i teenistuskoera kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Security staff shall also carry the required permit to carry weapons or special equipment or to use a service dog. </inglise>
<eesti>(28.06.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 62, 1056) </eesti>
<inglise>(28.06.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 62, 1056) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja v&auml;lja&otilde;pe ja t&auml;ienduskoolitus </eesti>
<inglise>Training and in-service training of security staff </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevuslitsents turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;ienduskoolitusega tegelemiseks antakse Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Activity licences for providing training and in-service training of security staff shall be issued pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikutel, kes tegelevad turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajate turvaalase v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;ienduskoolitusega, peab olema turvaettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i sisevalveteenistuse juhi v&otilde;i turvaala juhtivt&ouml;&ouml;taja kvalifikatsioonitunnistus ja politsei poolt v&auml;lja antud kehtiv turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaart (paragrahv 9). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who provides security-related training and in-service training for security staff shall hold a qualification certificate of the head of a security undertaking or internal guarding service or a qualification certificate of a senior security official, and a valid security guard identification card issued by the police (&sect; 9). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relvalve turvateenistuse osutamise &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision of provision of security services </inglise>
<eesti>(26.06.96 j&otilde;ust.26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.06.96 entered into force 26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet turvateenuste osutamise n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise &uuml;le teostab Politseiamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State supervision over compliance with the requirements regarding the provision of security services shall be organised by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiameti volitatud ametiisikutel on &otilde;igus peatada turvalitsentsi v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaardi kehtivus kuni kuueks kuuks v&otilde;i nende kehtivus t&uuml;histada juhul, kui turvateenistuse subjekt v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja: </eesti>
<inglise>Authorised officials of the Police Board have the right to suspend a security licence or security guard identification card for up to six months or to revoke a security licence or security guard identification card if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei t&auml;ida k&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tteid v&otilde;i tegutseb avalikku korda eirates v&otilde;i riigi julgeolekut ohustades; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a subject of security service or a security guard fails to comply with the provisions of this Act, ignores public order or poses a threat to national security; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei vasta enam n&otilde;uetele, mis oli turvalitsentsi v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaardi v&auml;ljaandmise aluseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a subject of security service or a security guard no longer complies with the requirements which were the basis for the issue of the security licence or security guard identification card; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui turvaettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i sisevalveteenistuse tegevus on katkenud rohkem kui kuueks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the activities of the security undertaking or internal guarding service have been discontinued for more than six months. </inglise>
<eesti>(26.06.96 j&otilde;ust.26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.06.96 entered into force 26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvalitsentsi v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kaardi v&auml;ljaandjal on &otilde;igus litsentsi v&otilde;i kaardi kehtivuse peatamise v&otilde;i t&uuml;histamise asemel teha turvateenistuse subjektile v&otilde;i turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajale kirjalik hoiatus, kui avastatud rikkumine on suhteliselt v&auml;ike v&otilde;i on toime pandud ettevaatamatuse t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The issuer of a security licence or security guard identification card has the right to issue a written warning to the subject of security service or the security guard instead of suspending or revoking the licence or identification card in the cases where a detected violation is relatively minor or was committed due to negligence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenistuse subjekti ja turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of subject of security service and security staff </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenistuse subjekt ja turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja kannavad vastutust seaduses ja/v&otilde;i lepingus etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Subjects of security service and security staff are held liable pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law and/or a contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja tagatised ja &otilde;iguslik kaitse </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees for and legal protection of security staff </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellele t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel tekitati seoses kallaletungiga kehavigastus, mis p&otilde;hjustas invaliidistumise, maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hekordset toetust allj&auml;rgnevalt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A security guard who is disabled due to a bodily injury resulting from an attack while performing his or her duties shall be paid a single allowance by the employer as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) I ja II grupi invaliidsuse korral - kahe ja poole aasta palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a category I or II disabled person shall be paid an amount equal to his or her two and a half years' salary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) III grupi invaliidsuse korral - &uuml;he aasta palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a category III disabled person shall be paid an amount equal to his or her one year's salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turvat&ouml;&ouml;taja hukkumisel t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel kallaletungi tagaj&auml;rjel maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja tema &uuml;lalpidamisel olevatele perekonnaliikmetele v&otilde;i omastele &uuml;hekordset toetust viie aasta palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a security guard dies as a result of an attack while performing his or her duties, his or her employer shall pay the family members or relatives who were maintained by him or her a single allowance to the extent of five years' salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 2.l&otilde;ikes m&auml;rgitud toetuste arvutamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for calculation of the allowances specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kellelgi pole &otilde;igust kohustada turvat&ouml;&ouml;tajat t&auml;itma seadusega vastuolus olevaid &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) No person has the right to demand that a security guard performs duties which are contrary to law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigi turvateenistus </eesti>
<inglise>Foreign security services </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigi turvateenistus v&otilde;ib Eestis ajutiselt osutada turvateenuseid v&otilde;i t&auml;ita turva&uuml;lesandeid Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud juhtudel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Foreign security services may temporarily provide security services or perform security tasks in Estonia in the cases and pursuant to the procedure established by the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Seniste valveettev&otilde;tete, -talituste ja -t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tegevuse, valvet&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;ienduskoolituse ning neile esitatud n&otilde;uete k&auml;esoleva seadusega koosk&otilde;lla viimise korra ja t&auml;htajad kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus, kusjuures koosk&otilde;lla viimise t&auml;htaeg ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada &uuml;hte aastat, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure and term for bringing the activities of existing guarding firms, guarding divisions and guards, the training and in-service training of guards, and the requirements provided thereon into accordance with this Act shall be established by the Government of the Republic; such term shall not exceed one year as of the entry into force of this Act. (1) RT = Riigi Teataja = State Gazette </inglise>
